title: MULTIFUNCTIONAL MOLECULAR MATERIALS
description: Author: Lahcene Ouahab Edition: 1 edition Publication Date: January 24, 2013 Publisher: Pan Stanford ISBN-10: 9814364290 ISBN-13: 978-9814364294 Pages: 314 pages Format: pdf Size: 14M --- This book provides a comprehensive overview on multifunctional molecular materials that involve coexistence or interplay or synergy between multiple physical properties focusing on electrical conductivity, magnetism, single-molecule magnets behavior, chirality, spin crossover, and luminescence. The book’s coverage ranges from transition metals and lanthanide coordination complexes to genuine organic materials. The book also discusses some potentialities of applications of these materials in molecule-based devices. --- http://dlfeb.com/book/multifunctional-molecular-materials/
